HEADWORD: Xiphodon
<hw>Xiph"o*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>xi`fos</grk> a sword + <grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, a
tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of
artiodactylous mammals found in the European Tertiary formations. It had
slender legs, didactylous feet, and small canine teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xiphoid</ent>⟦br⟧
